						<summary>

						<p>Pillar in the <hi rend="italic">maṇḍapa</hi> on the way to the temple of the goddess (Aṁbā).</p>						

						<p>This undated epigraph may be assigned to the 14-15th centuries, on the basis of palaeography.</p>						

						<p>It states that the <hi rend="italic">gōpura</hi> was the gift of Vidyādhara Mahāpātra, the devoted servant of god Mallēśvara of Śrīparvata, and that it was constructed under the supervision of Dōmāyidēva by the artisan Nāgaramahārāṇa.</p>						

						</summary>
